column5: planning to head out tommorow to cooks bay, only second trip to the bay, first time i got no perch, no nothing, i really hope to catch something other then cold feet, was thinking keswick, closer to shore, deeper?  where is the lakefish and whities hot spot now?  thnx

try this its up to date fishing info from the gilford side...right across the bay from keswick..  www.cooksbayfishingboard.com   everything you need to know,plus a video of the day, right now they are around 20-25ft of water,and they are hitting good today    cheers  good-luck
the Key will likely be to move around... I was out Saturday and we had pretty good success (60 or so fish) and countless missed fish. Keep on moving till you find a spot that produces... good luck!
